2)2 Write a Python program to check whether a string Starts with a capital 
letter, Ends with a digit and contain at least one special character. Display 
appropriate messages.
import string

s = input("Enter a string: ")
special_characters = string.punctuation
if s[0].isupper():
 print("String starts with a capital letter.")
else:
 print("String does not start with a capital letter.")
if s[-1].isdigit():
 print("String ends with a digit.")
else:
 print("String does not end with a digit.")
if any(char in special_characters for char in s):
 print("String contains at least one special character.")
else:
 print("String does not contain any special character.")

